params._latitude: Latitude part of the venue's coordinates.
params._longitude: Longitude part of the venue's coordinates.

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

returns._0: The URI of the contract-level metadata.

params._venueId: Unique identifier of the venue wishing to deregister.

returns.latitude: Latitude part of the venue's coordinates.
returns.longitude: Longitude part of the venue's coordinates.
returns.name: Name of the venue.

returns._0: VenueInfo Struct containing all relevant data of the venue.

params.venueAddress: Address of the venue to check.

returns.isRegistered: True if the venue is registered, false otherwise.

params.nominee: The address being nominated as a venue.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.tokenId: The token ID for which to set the URI

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params._latitude: New latitude for the venue's location.
params._longitude: New longitude for the venue's location.
params._streetAddress: New street address of the venue.
params._totalCapacity: New total capacity of the venue.
params._wallet: New wallet address of the venue.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

params.tokenId: The token ID of the artist.

returns._0: The URI associated with the artist token.

acceptNomination(string,string,int256,in.notice: Accepts the nomination to become a registered venue.

contractURI().notice: Retrieves the URI for the contract metadata.

deregisterVenue(uint256).notice: Allows a venue to deregister themselves from the registry.

getVenue(address).notice: Retrieves information about a venue using their wallet address.

getVenueById(uint256).notice: Retrieves venue information by its unique identifier.

isVenueRegistered(address).notice: Checks if a venue is registered in the registry.

nominate(address).notice: Nominates another address as a venue, provided the caller has sufficient referral credits.

nominatedVenues(address).notice: Tracks which addresses have been nominated as venues.

setContractURI(string).notice: Sets or updates the URI for the venue contract.

setTokenURI(uint256,string).notice: Sets the URI for a given token ID

updateVenue(uint256,string,string,addres.notice: Allows a registered venue to update their profile information.

uri(uint256).notice: Retrieves the URI for a specific artist's token.
